snippet.textDisplay:
Just trying to help someone, upvote so people can see. This company is not from my country or anything, but this should not be allowed.


"I just bought a $3,000 pc from IBUYPOWER.COM and I got completely screwed by them.

I bought a Ryzen 3950x and a NVIDIA 2080 SUPER and they sent me the PC without windows installed, none of the keyboards I tried worked as I had to hold down each key for 3 seconds for the computer to respond to it, the liquid cooler has deep metal scratches on the edges, after the 3rd time I turned it on the fans started hitting something and making a loud and horrible noise.... when is sent it back the technician emailed me a receipt for $750 dollars for a brand new GPU because the one they originally put in my PC was ALSO DEFECTIVE. Then they tried charging me for it?? They also charged me for packaging at FedEx and when I called them about it and told them I didn’t want to pay another $35 for packaging and they should cover it because it’s their fault I have to send it back... the head manager told me I shouldn’t have thrown away the packaging and that it’s my fault. His name is Jeff (no meme intended). When I asked him to speak to someone else he said no he was the highest person in the whole company I could talk to. The other customer service agents told me their assembly line has certain quotas and they get bonuses for shipping out as many PCs as possible so they do crappy jobs to finish them but when they get PCs sent back to them (which sounded like a regular thing) one guy is responsible for only a couple of PCs and he can be more thorough.

Oh yeah Jeff as well as other customer service and technical support reps told me they don’t make mistakes like that and that ALL happened during shipping and that it’s FedExs fault. And I said “how tf can fed ex cause deep metal on metal scratches to a liquid cooling system inside a PC that has its internals completely protected by expandable foam with tempered glass only a few inches away? Wouldn’t the outside of the PC be damaged as well if it we FedExs fault? Did FedEx also uninstall windows too?”

The technical support guy said “yes”

I threatened Jeff with reporting them to the BBB and convincing the internet to stay away from them because they’re ripping people off by sending them unfinished or damaged products and no one is taking responsibility or accountability and then telling me IM at fault for throwing away the packaging? And he told me if that’s what I want to do then to do so. Not a single person I talked to over the course of two weeks once apologized or asked what they could do to help me. Only after I threatened to sue them did they say there would be no mistakes when I got the PC back.

All in all stay FAR AWAY from IBUYPOWER. Please.

Also please upvote this so others can see this. Thanks."
Mr Feathers
